   legacy    chatterton 's genius and his death are commemorated by percy bysshe shelley in adonais ( though its main emphasis is the commemoration of keats ) , by william wordsworth in " resolution and independence , " by samuel taylor coleridge in " monody on the death of chatterton , " by dante gabriel rossetti in " five english poets , " and in john keats ' sonnet "

literary johns : he dedicated his " endymion " to thomas chatterton , a poet who killed himself at the age of 17

